$$ \sin^{-1} (\sin 3) + \sin^{-1} (\sin 4) + \sin^{-1} (\sin 5). $$

$$ \sin 3 = \sin (3 - 2 \pi) = \sin (3 - 4 \pi) = \cdots $$
We have
$$ \sin^{-1} (\sin x) = \begin{cases} x, & x \in \left[ -\frac{\pi}{2}, \frac{\pi}{2} \right] \\ \pi - x, & x \in \left[ \frac{\pi}{2}, \frac{3 \pi}{2} \right] \end{cases} $$
$3 \approx 3.14$, $\pi \approx 3.14$.
$4 = 3.14 + 0.86$ and $5 \approx 3.14 + 1.86$.
Since $3 \in \left[ 0, \pi \right]$, we have $\sin 3 > 0$ and $3 < \pi$.
$$ 3 \approx 3.14 \implies \sin 3 \approx \sin (3.14) = 0. $$
$$ 3 \in \left[ -\frac{\pi}{2}, \frac{\pi}{2} \right] \implies \sin^{-1} (\sin 3) = 3. $$
$$ \sin^{-1} (\sin 4) $$
We have $4 = 2 \pi + 2 \approx 6.283 + 2 = 8.283$, and $\sin(4) \approx \sin(0.86). $
Since $4 \in \left( 3 \pi / 2, 2 \pi \right)$, $4$ is in the 4th quadrant.
We have
$$ 4 = \pi + (4-\pi) \approx 3.14 + (0.86) = 3.14 + 0.86 = 4, $$
so $4 = \pi + (4-\pi) \approx 4 - \pi \approx 0.86$.
Since $\sin 4$ is negative and $|\sin 4| < 1$, we have
$\sin^{-1} (\sin 4) = \pi - 4 \approx \pi - 4 \approx \pi - \pi - \pi = - \pi \approx -3.14$.
$2 \pi \approx 6.28$
$3 \approx 3.14$, $4 \approx 3.14 + 0.86$.
$\pi \approx 3.14$. $3 = \pi - 0.14$.
$\pi = 3.14$, $3 - \pi = -0.14$, $\sin^{-1} \sin 3 = 3$.
$\sin 4 \approx \sin (4-2\pi) \approx \sin(4 - 6.283) \approx \sin(-2.28)$.
$\sin^{-1} (\sin 4) = \pi - 4$
$$ \sin^{-1} (\sin 3) = 3, \sin^{-1} (\sin 4) = \pi - 4, \sin^{-1} (\sin 5) = 5 - 2 \pi $$
$3+\pi-4+5-2 \pi = 4-\pi$

Final Answer: $\boxed{4}$
